archaea, and has now been engineered as RNA guided endonucleases (RGENs) for genome
c
iediting. Typically, a type II CRISPR system functions by the CRISPR RNA (crRNA)
tinteracting with a trans-activating crRNA (tracrRNA) to form a crRNA:tracrRNA duplex
(this RNA duplex could be replaced with a single guide RNA, sgRNA), which directs
