indels towards HDR-mediated modifications. Although the site mutation or knockin event
can be achieved at high rates in cells and animals by providing a single-stranded DNA or a
e
double-strand DNA plasmid as template, how to reduce the NHEJ-mediated indels and
l
improve the HDR-mediated precise modification are still the interesting issues.
c
Co-localization of the template DNA with Cas9:sgRNA complex to the target site to enhance
i
HDR or use the siRNA or inhibitor of NHEJ-mediated repair pathway to reduce the
t
competing NHEJ should be very helpful.
r
Another, but not the last, important problem is to efficiently deliver CRISPR/Cas9 system
into those cell types or tissues that are hard to transfect and/or infect. The development of
A
safe gene delivery vehicles is necessary for the versatile use of CRISPR/Cas9 system.
Undoubtedly, the basic research will make its way into clinic practise. Further optimization
d
and development of next-generation CRISPR/Cas9 tools for genome and epigenome editing
eisexpected to satisfy the requirement of the therapeutic applications.
